cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.RO, cs.LG, cs.CL. 

The paper proposes a model that maps raw visual observations to goals and generates actions required to complete them. This involves using language-conditioned image generation networks and training the model from demonstration only without external resources. Therefore, the paper is likely to belong to the following sub-categories: 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as the paper proposes a model that involves goal prediction and action generation. 
- cs.CV (Computer Vision) as the model uses raw visual observations to generate goals and actions. 
- cs.RO (Robotics) as the paper involves generating actions to complete tasks in a 3D environment. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) as the model is trained from demonstration only without external resources. 
- cs.CL (Computation and Language) as the paper involves using language-conditioned image generation networks.
